    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect size calculation in get_crc_indication_size function\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_crc_indication_size` function in `nr_fapi_p7_utils.c` was using an incorrect formula to calculate the size needed for CB CRC status bits. This caused overallocation of memory when the number of CBs was a multiple of 8. The same bug was present in several related functions and has been fixed consistently across the codebase.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Fixed size calculation formula from `x / 8 + 1` to `(x + 7) / 8` in multiple functions:\n  - `get_crc_indication_size()` - primary fix\n  - `copy_crc_indication_CRC()`\n  - `eq_crc_indication_CRC()`\n  - `dump_crc_indication()`\n  - UCI indication functions for SR, HARQ, CSI Part 1 & 2\n  - PUSCH-related functions\n  - All equality, copy, and dump functions for these structures\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing CRC indications with a number of CBs that is a multiple of 8 (e.g., 8, 16, 24 CBs), the function would allocate 1 extra byte per CRC entry. For example, with 8 CBs, the function would allocate 2 bytes instead of the correct 1 byte needed to store 8 bits. This leads to memory waste and inconsistent behavior between size calculations and actual memory allocation in related functions.\n\n"
}